{
  "texts": [
    "Constraint-based APR methods utilize constraint specifications to guide the repair by converting the repair problems into a constraint solver problem.",
    "For example, SemFix [105] fixes single-line bugs using symbolic execution by crafting repair constraints.",
    "DirectFix [102] improves patch generation with constraint solving and program synthesis, extending the ability to fix multi-line bugs but suffering from the scalability problem due to maxSMT solving overheads.",
    "To overcome this, Angelix [103] proposes to employ the lightweight value based specifications (angelic forest) for better scalability.",
    "Nopol [161] was proposed to fix if-conditional bugs using SMT."
  ]
}